title.en: VPR data from the Scotian Shelf
title.fr: Donn饳 VPR de l'鴡g貥 n鯭飯ssaise

eventID.definition: An identifier for the set of information associated with a dwc:Event (something that occurs at a place and time). May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to the data set.

minimumDepthInMeters.definition: The lesser depth of a range of depth below the local

maximumDepthInMeters.definition: The greater depth of a range of depth below the local

DEPHPRST.definition: Depth (spatial coordinate) of sampling event start relative to water surface in the water body by profiling pressure sensor and conversion to depth using unspecified algorithm

individualCount.definition: The number of individuals present at the time of the dwc:Occurrence.

verbatimIdentification.definition: A string representing the taxonomic identification as it appeared in the original record.

SDBIOL01.definition: Abundance of biological entity specified elsewhere per unit volume of the water body

TEMPST01.definition: Temperature of the water body by CTD or STD

PSALST01.definition: Practical salinity of the water body by CTD and computation using UNESCO 1983 algorithm

POTDENS0.definition: Density (potential) of the water body by computation from salinity and potential temperature using UNESCO algorithm with 0 decibar reference pressure

TURBXXXX.definition: Turbidity of water in the water body

sampleSizeValue.definition: A numeric value for a measurement of the size (time duration, length, area, or volume) of a sample in a sampling dwc:Event.

sampleSizeUnit.definition: The unit of measurement of the size (time duration, length, area, or volume) of a sample in a sampling dwc:Event.

scientificName.definition: The full scientific name, with authorship and date information if known. When forming part of a dwc:Identification, this should be the name in lowest level taxonomic rank that can be determined. This term should not contain identification qualifications, which should instead be supplied in the dwc:identificationQualifier term.

identifiedBy.definition: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organisations who assigned the Taxon to the subject.

identificationVerificationStatus.definition: A categorical indicator of the extent to which the taxonomic identification has been verified to be correct.

depthDifferenceMeters.definition: Difference between maximumDepthInMeters and minimumDepthInMeters of an individual data bin, in meters

minimumTimeSeconds.definition: minimum time value in a data bin, measured in seconds from the start of the day of sampling

maximumTimeSeconds.definition: maximum time value in a data bin, measured in seconds from the start of the day of sampling

timeDifferenceSeconds.definition: Difference between maximumTimeSeconds and minimumTimeSeconds of an individual data bin, in seconds

numberOfFrames.definition: number of VPR frames captured within an individual data bin

timeMilliseconds.definition: Time measured in milliseconds since the start of the sampling day

towyoID.definition: A string identifying the section of the cast to which the data point belongs

maximumCastDepthInMeters.definition: Maximum depth in Meters of the cast dataset
